ciscoQpLbgMIB.name: ciscoQpLbgMIB

revisions.description: The table cqlqamPartitionTable describes the various parameters of QP such as QP's state, protocol, management IP, server IP, server state, associated QAM details and configured video route details. The table cqlloadBalanceGroupTable describes the LBG parameters such as total bandwidth, available bandwidth and reserved bandwidth of QAM & IP based sessions. The table cqllbgrouteTable describes the destination IP, udp range, reserved bandwidth of routes configured under LBG and flow count per route. Following objects were added to the MIB to provide trap notification support for the over subscribed Qam. cqlQamOverSubscribedAlert cqlQamOverSubscribedEnable Added object cqlqpServerIpList of type OCTET STRING for displaying multiple server IP's.
Latest version of this MIB module.

ciscoQpLbgMIB.description: This MIB module represents the Qam-Partition (QP) and Load Balance Group (LBG) parameters in the headend and it is supported by an snmp agent. It defines objects for managing both QP and LBG.

cqlQpStateChange.name: cqlQpStateChange
cqlQpStateChange.description: The device generates this notification when a QP state has changed and the value of cqlQpNotifyEnable is 'true'.

cqlQamAdd.name: cqlQamAdd
cqlQamAdd.description: The device generates this notification when a qam has been added to QP and the value of cqlQamNotifyEnable is 'true'.

cqlQamDelete.name: cqlQamDelete
cqlQamDelete.description: The device generates this notification when a qam has been deleted from QP and the value of cqlQamNotifyEnable is 'true'.

cqlLbgRouteAdd.name: cqlLbgRouteAdd
cqlLbgRouteAdd.description: The device generates this notification when a route has been added to QP and the value of cqlRouteNotifyEnable is 'true'.

cqlLbgRouteDelete.name: cqlLbgRouteDelete
cqlLbgRouteDelete.description: The device generates this notification when a route has been deleted from QP and the value of cqlRouteNotifyEnable is 'true'.

cqlQamOverSubscribedAlert.name: cqlQamOverSubscribedAlert
cqlQamOverSubscribedAlert.description: The device generates this notification when a qam has been oversubscribed or cleared. This will be enabled when the object cqlQamOverSubscribedEnable is set to 'true'.

cqlqamPartitionTable.name: cqlqamPartitionTable
cqlqamPartitionTable.description: This table describes the various parameters of QP such as QP's state, protocol, management IP, server IP, server state, information related to qam and video routes.

cqlqamPartitionEntry.name: cqlqamPartitionEntry
cqlqamPartitionEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to the configuration of a QP.

cqlqpIndex.name: cqlqpIndex
cqlqpIndex.description: Table Index. This index uniquely identifies the QP.

cqlqpId.name: cqlqpId
cqlqpId.description: This object specifies the QP Id.

cqlqpMgmtIpAddrType.name: cqlqpMgmtIpAddrType
cqlqpMgmtIpAddrType.description: The type of the Management address as defined inetAddressType. The supported address types are IPv4 and IPv6.

cqlqpMgmtIp.name: cqlqpMgmtIp
cqlqpMgmtIp.description: This object specifies the Management IP address of a QP.

cqlqpServerIpAddrType.name: cqlqpServerIpAddrType
cqlqpServerIpAddrType.description: The type of the Server address as defined inetAddressType. The supported address types are IPv4 and IPv6.

cqlqpState.name: cqlqpState
cqlqpState.description: This object specifies the state of the QP. The following are the valid states. inactive(1) QP is in inactive state. init(2) QP is in init state. active(3) QP is in active state.

cqlqpProtocol.name: cqlqpProtocol
cqlqpProtocol.description: This object specifies the QP Protocol. Gqi(1) Ermi(2)

cqlqpKeepAliveTime.name: cqlqpKeepAliveTime
cqlqpKeepAliveTime.description: This object specifies the keepalive timer in seconds for a QP.

cqlqpServerState.name: cqlqpServerState
cqlqpServerState.description: This object specifies the Server state of the QP. disconnected(1) Server is in disconnected state. connected(2) Server is in connected state.

cqlqpGqiMacAddr.name: cqlqpGqiMacAddr
cqlqpGqiMacAddr.description: This object specifies the MAC address of a QP, applicable only for GQI Protocol.

cqlqpGqiResetInterval.name: cqlqpGqiResetInterval
cqlqpGqiResetInterval.description: This object specifies Reset interval for a QP. It is applicable only for GQI protocol.

cqlqpNumQams.name: cqlqpNumQams
cqlqpNumQams.description: The total number of qams associated with the QP.

cqlqpQamCarrrierList.name: cqlqpQamCarrrierList
cqlqpQamCarrrierList.description: This object specifies the list of Qam carriers associated with the QP.

cqlqpNumRoutes.name: cqlqpNumRoutes
cqlqpNumRoutes.description: The total number of routes associated with the QP.

cqlqpRouteDetails.name: cqlqpRouteDetails
cqlqpRouteDetails.description: Route details of the QP. It includes the configured IP and also the highest and lowest UDP range.

cqlqpErmiErrpComponentName.name: cqlqpErmiErrpComponentName
cqlqpErmiErrpComponentName.description: Component Name for the QP, applicable only for ERMI protocol.

cqlqpErmiErrpStreamingZone.name: cqlqpErmiErrpStreamingZone
cqlqpErmiErrpStreamingZone.description: Streaming zone for the QP, applicable only for ERMI protocol.

cqlqpErmiErrpHoldTime.name: cqlqpErmiErrpHoldTime
cqlqpErmiErrpHoldTime.description: Hold Time in seconds for the QP, applicable only for ERMI protocol.

cqlqpErmiErrpConnnectTime.name: cqlqpErmiErrpConnnectTime
cqlqpErmiErrpConnnectTime.description: Connect Time in seconds for the QP, applicable only for ERMI protocol.

cqlqpErmiErrpConnectRetry.name: cqlqpErmiErrpConnectRetry
cqlqpErmiErrpConnectRetry.description: Connection retry in seconds for the QP. It is applicable only for ERMI protocol.

cqlqpErmiRtspConnectTime.name: cqlqpErmiRtspConnectTime
cqlqpErmiRtspConnectTime.description: Connect time in seconds for the QP. It is applicable only for ERMI protocol.

cqlqpErmiRtspConnectRetry.name: cqlqpErmiRtspConnectRetry
cqlqpErmiRtspConnectRetry.description: Connect retry in seconds for the QP, applicable only for ERMI protocol.

cqlqpErmiRtspKeepAliveTime.name: cqlqpErmiRtspKeepAliveTime
cqlqpErmiRtspKeepAliveTime.description: Connection timeout in seconds for the QP. It is applicable only for ERMI protocol.

cqlqpErmiRtspSessionTimeout.name: cqlqpErmiRtspSessionTimeout
cqlqpErmiRtspSessionTimeout.description: Session Timeout in seconds for the QP. It is applicable only for ERMI protocol.

cqlqpQamOversubscribedStatus.name: cqlqpQamOversubscribedStatus
cqlqpQamOversubscribedStatus.description: This object specifies oversubscription status of a Qam. The value 'True' indicates the Qam is oversubscribed. Otherwise the value 'False' is reported.

cqlqpServerIpList.name: cqlqpServerIpList
cqlqpServerIpList.description: List of Server IP's for the QP.

cqlloadBalanceGroupTable.name: cqlloadBalanceGroupTable
cqlloadBalanceGroupTable.description: This table describes the total bandwidth and the reserved bandwidth of QAM/IP based sessions.

cqlloadBalanceGroupEntry.name: cqlloadBalanceGroupEntry
cqlloadBalanceGroupEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to the parameters of a LBG.

cqllbgIndex.name: cqllbgIndex
cqllbgIndex.description: This index is to identify the LBG group within the slot.

cqllbgTotalBandwidth.name: cqllbgTotalBandwidth
cqllbgTotalBandwidth.description: This object specifies the total bandwidth in Kbps of a LBG.

cqllbgQamRsvBandwidth.name: cqllbgQamRsvBandwidth
cqllbgQamRsvBandwidth.description: This object specifies the total reserved bandwidth in Kbps for depi sessions.

cqllbgIpRsvBandwidth.name: cqllbgIpRsvBandwidth
cqllbgIpRsvBandwidth.description: This object specifies the total reserved bandwidth in Kbps for video sessions.

cqllbgAvailableBandwidth.name: cqllbgAvailableBandwidth
cqllbgAvailableBandwidth.description: This object specifies the available bandwidth in Kbps. This may be calculated as (TotalBandwidth - (QamRsvBandwidth + IpRsvBandwith)).

cqllbgrouteTable.name: cqllbgrouteTable
cqllbgrouteTable.description: This table describes the route parameters such as QP id,destination ip, low and high udp range, reserved and allocated bandwidth.

cqllbgrouteEntry.name: cqllbgrouteEntry
cqllbgrouteEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to the parameters of a route.

cqllbgRouteIndex.name: cqllbgRouteIndex
cqllbgRouteIndex.description: The table index. This is the index which uniquely identifies the route within the LBG group.

cqllbgQpId.name: cqllbgQpId
cqllbgQpId.description: This object specifies the QP ID. The range of the QP is between 1 and 50.

cqllbgDstIpAddrType.name: cqllbgDstIpAddrType
cqllbgDstIpAddrType.description: The type of the destination address as defined inetAddressType. The supported address types are IPv4 and IPv6.

cqllbgDstIpAddr.name: cqllbgDstIpAddr
cqllbgDstIpAddr.description: Destination IP address of the route to which the incoming packets are routed to.

cqllbgUdpPortRangeMin.name: cqllbgUdpPortRangeMin
cqllbgUdpPortRangeMin.description: The lowest UDP port of the UDP port range that can be used.

cqllbgUdpPortRangeMax.name: cqllbgUdpPortRangeMax
cqllbgUdpPortRangeMax.description: The highest UDP port of the UDP port range that can be used.

cqllbgGqiIngressPort.name: cqllbgGqiIngressPort
cqllbgGqiIngressPort.description: Ingress port of a QP, applicable only for GQI protocol.

cqllbgRsvBandwidth.name: cqllbgRsvBandwidth
cqllbgRsvBandwidth.description: Reserved bandwidth is the total bitrate reserved on this route in Kbps.

cqllbgAllocatedBandwidth.name: cqllbgAllocatedBandwidth
cqllbgAllocatedBandwidth.description: The total bandwidth being used by sessions using this route in Kbps.

cqllbgNumFlows.name: cqllbgNumFlows
cqllbgNumFlows.description: Number of sessions currently use this route to forward this traffic in Kbps.

cqlQpNotifyEnable.name: cqlQpNotifyEnable
cqlQpNotifyEnable.description: This object specifies whether the system generates cqlQpStateChange notifications. A false value will prevent cqlQpStateChange notifications from being generated by this system.

cqlQamNotifyEnable.name: cqlQamNotifyEnable
cqlQamNotifyEnable.description: This object specifies whether the system generates cqlQamAdd or cqlQamDelete notifications. A false value will prevent cqlQamAdd or cqlQamDelete notifications from being generated by this system.

cqlRouteNotifyEnable.name: cqlRouteNotifyEnable
cqlRouteNotifyEnable.description: This object specifies whether the system produces cqlRouteAdd or cqlRouteDelete notifications. A false value will prevent cqlRouteAdd or cqlRouteDelete notifications from being generated by this system.

cqlQamOverSubscribedEnable.name: cqlQamOverSubscribedEnable
cqlQamOverSubscribedEnable.description: This object specifies whether the system produces cqlQamOverSubscribedAlert notifications. A false value will prevent cqlQamOverSubscribedAlert notifications from being generated by the system.

cqlciscoQpLbgCompliance.name: cqlciscoQpLbgCompliance
cqlciscoQpLbgCompliance.description: These objects describe the support level for QP and LBG.

cqlciscoQpLbgCompliance1.name: cqlciscoQpLbgCompliance1
cqlciscoQpLbgCompliance1.description: These objects describe the support level for QP and LBG.

cqlciscoQpNotifsGroup.name: cqlciscoQpNotifsGroup
cqlciscoQpNotifsGroup.description: A collection of QP notifications that may optionally be implemented. cqlciscoQpNotifsGroup object is superseded by cqlciscoQpNotifsGroup1.

cqlciscoLbgNotifsGroup.name: cqlciscoLbgNotifsGroup
cqlciscoLbgNotifsGroup.description: A collection of LBG notifications that may optionally be implemented.

cqlciscoQpObjectGroup.name: cqlciscoQpObjectGroup
cqlciscoQpObjectGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about the QP parameters. cqlciscoQpObjectGroup object is superseded by cqlciscoQpObjectGroup1.

cqlciscoLbgObjectGroup.name: cqlciscoLbgObjectGroup
cqlciscoLbgObjectGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about the LBG parameters.

cqlciscoLbgRouteObjectGroup.name: cqlciscoLbgRouteObjectGroup
cqlciscoLbgRouteObjectGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about the LBG route parameters.

cqlciscoQpLbgNotifsControlGroup.name: cqlciscoQpLbgNotifsControlGroup
cqlciscoQpLbgNotifsControlGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about the notification enables. cqlciscoQpLbgNotifsControlGroup object is superseded by cqlciscoQpLbgNotifsControlGroup1.

cqlciscoQpNotifsGroup1.name: cqlciscoQpNotifsGroup1
cqlciscoQpNotifsGroup1.description: A collection of QP notifications that may optionally be implemented.

cqlciscoQpObjectGroup1.name: cqlciscoQpObjectGroup1
cqlciscoQpObjectGroup1.description: A collection of objects providing information about the QP parameters.

cqlciscoQpLbgNotifsControlGroup1.name: cqlciscoQpLbgNotifsControlGroup1
cqlciscoQpLbgNotifsControlGroup1.description: A collection of objects providing information about the notification enables.
